{"id": "als1665702995258", "title": "Configure the Uniface Web Application Server on iSeries", "breadcrumbs": ["Installing Uniface", "Installing and Configuring Uniface on iSeries", "Running Uniface Applications on iSeries", "Deploying Server Pages and Web Services on iSeries", "Configure the Uniface Web Application Server on iSeries"], "url": "https://docs.rocketsoftware.com/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/als1665702995258.html", "html": "<html><body><header class=\"zDocsTopicPageHead\"><h1 class=\"css-g931ng\">Configure the Uniface Web Application Server on iSeries</h1><div class=\"zDocsTopicActions\" role=\"list\"><div class=\"zDocsBundlePagination\" data-testid=\"next-prev-container\" role=\"listitem\"><div class=\"zDocsPrevTopicButton zDocsPrevTopicButton\"><span class=\"\"><a aria-label=\"Previous:   Deploying Server Pages and Web Services on iSeries \" class=\"\" data-tooltip-content=\"Previous:   Deploying Server Pages and Web Services on iSeries \" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" data-tooltip-open=\"false\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/evw1665702995189.html\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-prev\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-prev\"></use></svg></a></span></div><div class=\"zDocsNextTopicButton zDocsNextTopicButton\"><span class=\"\"><a aria-label=\"Next:   Create and Run a Test Service on iSeries \" class=\"\" data-tooltip-content=\"Next:   Create and Run a Test Service on iSeries \" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" data-tooltip-open=\"false\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qmw1665702995400.html\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></a></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsMyDocsMenu\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Add to My Topics\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Add to My Topics\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" id=\"addToMyDocsDropdownTrigger\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-bookmark-add\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-bookmark-add\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-bookmark-add\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-bookmark-add\"></use></svg>Add to My Topics</span><div aria-labelledby=\"pdfDropdown\" class=\"dropdown-menu dropdown-menu-right\"><a class=\"zDocsAddTopicButton zDocsMyDocsMenuItem dropdown-item\" href=\"/de-DE/auth/login?redirect=/bundle/uniface_104/page/als1665702995258.html?finish_action=mydocs_topic_and_sub\">Add selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsAddTopicButton zDocsMyDocsMenuItem dropdown-item\" href=\"/de-DE/auth/login?redirect=/bundle/uniface_104/page/als1665702995258.html?finish_action=mydocs_topic_and_sub_head\">Add Topic &amp; Subtopics with topic head</a><a class=\"zDocsAddTopicButton zDocsMyDocsMenuItem dropdown-item\" href=\"/de-DE/auth/login?redirect=/bundle/uniface_104/page/als1665702995258.html?finish_action=mydocs_pub\">Add entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsWatchButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Watch\" class=\"d-lg-flex d-none zDocsSubscribeButton\" data-tooltip-content=\"Watch\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-eye\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-eye\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsSubscribeButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-eye zDocsSubscribeButton\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-eye\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsSubscribeButton\">Watch</span></span></div><div class=\"zDocsExportPdfMenu zDocsExportMenu\" data-testid=\"export-pdf-menu\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Download PDF\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Download PDF\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-pdf\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-pdf\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#ZdExportPDFModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-pdf\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-pdf\"></use></svg>Download PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2525758\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2525758\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 11, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104als1665702995258.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/als1665702995258.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/als1665702995258.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"als1665702995258\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Configure the Uniface Web Application Server on iSeries\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">To be able to deploy Uniface web applications on the iSeries, you must configure the Uniface Web Application Server so that it can correctly locate and run web components. To do so, you need to ensure that assignment files of the Uniface Router, Uniface Server, and client assignment file match the Web Application Server defined in the <span class=\"ph filepath\">web.xml</span> file.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section context\" id=\"als1665702995258__context_w2951ab1b5b1_w2952ab1b5_w2953ab1\">\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"als1665702995258__li_d29207e1_d29208e1_d29209e1\">In the <span class=\"ph filepath\">web.xml</span> file, the last element in the connection string is the UST used by the Uniface Router to start a Uniface Server. It is set to <code class=\"ph codeph\">wasv</code> by default.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"als1665702995258__li_d29210e1_d29211e1_d29212e1\">In the Uniface Router's assignment file, the [SERVER] section of the Uniface Router's assignment file has an entry for <code class=\"ph codeph\">wasv</code>, such as the following:\n <div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">wasv = userver -asn=wasv.asn</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"als1665702995258__p_d66614e1_d66615e1_d66616e1\">The Uniface Router (UROUTER) starts a new Uniface Server (USERVER) instance when it receives its first request for UST <code class=\"ph codeph\">wasv</code>.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"als1665702995258__li_d29213e1_d29214e1_d29215e1\">The USERVER assignment file <span class=\"ph filepath\">wasv.asn</span> contains the settings and paths or file redirections required to correctly run the web application components.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"als1665702995258__li_d29216e1_d29217e1_d29218e1\">The client assignment file must define a path to the iSeries where the components will be executed. The path must use the same UST <code class=\"ph codeph\">wasv</code> that is used in <span class=\"ph filepath\">web.xml</span>.\n </li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"als1665702995258__note_w2957ab1b5b1b3_w2958ab1b5b1_w2959ab1b5_w2960ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> The following instructions are for a test service called\n               <span class=\"ph filepath\">websrv.svc</span>, which will run on the iSeries and be called from a\n            form running in the Uniface IDE on a Windows client.</div>\n</section>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"als1665702995258__li_d29219e1_d29220e1_d29221e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"als1665702995258__p_d66617e1_d66618e1_d66619e1\">Edit the client assignment file, in this case <span class=\"ph filepath\">ide.asn</span>\n</span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"als1665702995258__li_d29222e1_d29223e1_d29224e1\">For this example, if you have <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$TEST_MODE_COMPONENTS</span> in your assignment file, temporarily comment it out.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"als1665702995258__li_d29225e1_d29226e1_d29227e1\">Add an entry to the [SERVICES_EXEC] section\n                     to direct the execution of the <span class=\"ph filepath\">websrv.svc</span> service to the\n                     UST <code class=\"ph codeph\">wasv</code>: <div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">[SERVICES_EXEC]\nWEBSRV $WASV:WEBSRV</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"als1665702995258__li_d29228e1_d29229e1_d29230e1\">Add an entry to the [PATHS] section to\n                     define the path to the <code class=\"ph codeph\">WASV</code> Uniface Server on the iSeries:\n                        <div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">[PATHS]\n$WASV TCP:<var class=\"keyword varname\">iSeriesNetworkName</var>+<var class=\"keyword varname\">Port</var>|<var class=\"keyword varname\">User</var>|<var class=\"keyword varname\">Password</var>|wasv</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div><p class=\"p\" id=\"als1665702995258__p_d66620e1_d66621e1_d66622e1\">The contents of this\n                           <code class=\"ph codeph\">$WASV</code> setting must be the same as that specified in the\n                           <span class=\"ph filepath\">web.xml</span> (see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qnb1665702995328.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qnb1665702995328.html\" title=\"The IBM Integrated Web application server for i can deploy applications that are in the form of a web archive file, .war file or a web application bundle .wab file. The Uniface Web Request Dispatcher (WRD) servlet is not in this format, so it must be packaged into a .war file.\">Configure the WRD and Create a wrd.war File on iSeries</a>),\n                        except for the following:</p><ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"als1665702995258__li_d29231e1_d29232e1_d29233e1\">Replace <code class=\"ph codeph\">UV8:</code> by\n                              <code class=\"ph codeph\">TCP:</code>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"als1665702995258__li_d29234e1_d29235e1_d29236e1\">If you used the literal\n                              ‘<code class=\"ph codeph\">localhost</code>’ in <span class=\"ph filepath\">web.xml</span>, replace\n                           it with the actual network name of your iSeries machine. </li>\n</ul><p class=\"p\" id=\"als1665702995258__p_d66623e1_d66624e1_d66625e1\">For example:\n                     </p><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">$WASV TCP:myAS400+13001|userver|userver|wasv</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"als1665702995258__li_d29237e1_d29238e1_d29239e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"als1665702995258__p_d66626e1_d66627e1_d66628e1\">Edit the assignment file of the Uniface Server (<span class=\"ph filepath\">wasv.asn</span>).\n Add an entry to the [RESOURCES] section to specify the location of the UARs containing the components. For example:</span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">[RESOURCES]\n; if the UAR is in member MY_UAR of file UAR:\nUNIFxxxx/my_uar.uar\n; if the UAR is in the IFS:\nIFS:/home/username/uars/my_uar.uar</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</li></ol></section>\n<section class=\"section result body required-cleanup-multiple-ol-elements-in-topic-body\" id=\"als1665702995258__result_w2954ab1b5b5_w2955ab1b5_w2956ab1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"als1665702995258__p_d66629e1_d66630e1_d66631e1\">You should now be able to create and test the <span class=\"ph filepath\">websrv.svc</span> service, as described in <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qmw1665702995400.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qmw1665702995400.html\" title=\"For testing purposes, create a test service that can be used as a web service on iSeries, and a form that can call the service.\">Create and Run a Test Service on iSeries</a> and <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"cul1665702995473.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/cul1665702995473.html\" title=\"After you have confirmed that the test service websrv.svc runs correctly, you can deploy it as a web service. To do so, you need to generate a WSDL file that describes the interface to web service clients that wish to invoke the service, and then configure the WRD to use this file.\">Run the Service as a Web Service</a>.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2525758\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2525758\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Configure the Uniface Web Application Server on iSeries Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 11, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Configure the Uniface Web Application Server on iSeries To be able to deploy Uniface web applications on the iSeries, you must configure the Uniface Web Application Server so that it can correctly locate and run web components. To do so, you need to ensure that assignment files of the Uniface Router, Uniface Server, and client assignment file match the Web Application Server defined in the web.xml file. In the web.xml file, the last element in the connection string is the UST used by the Uniface Router to start a Uniface Server. It is set to wasv by default. In the Uniface Router's assignment file, the [SERVER] section of the Uniface Router's assignment file has an entry for wasv , such as the following: wasv = userver -asn=wasv.asn Copy The Uniface Router (UROUTER) starts a new Uniface Server (USERVER) instance when it receives its first request for UST wasv . The USERVER assignment file wasv.asn contains the settings and paths or file redirections required to correctly run the web application components. The client assignment file must define a path to the iSeries where the components will be executed. The path must use the same UST wasv that is used in web.xml . Note: The following instructions are for a test service called websrv.svc , which will run on the iSeries and be called from a form running in the Uniface IDE on a Windows client. Edit the client assignment file, in this case ide.asn For this example, if you have $TEST_MODE_COMPONENTS in your assignment file, temporarily comment it out. Add an entry to the [SERVICES_EXEC] section to direct the execution of the websrv.svc service to the UST wasv : [SERVICES_EXEC] WEBSRV $WASV:WEBSRV Copy Add an entry to the [PATHS] section to define the path to the WASV Uniface Server on the iSeries: [PATHS] $WASV TCP: iSeriesNetworkName + Port | User | Password |wasv Copy The contents of this $WASV setting must be the same as that specified in the web.xml (see Configure the WRD and Create a wrd.war File on iSeries ), except for the following: Replace UV8: by TCP: If you used the literal ‘ localhost ’ in web.xml , replace it with the actual network name of your iSeries machine. For example: $WASV TCP:myAS400+13001|userver|userver|wasv Copy Edit the assignment file of the Uniface Server ( wasv.asn ). Add an entry to the [RESOURCES] section to specify the location of the UARs containing the components. For example: [RESOURCES] ; if the UAR is in member MY_UAR of file UAR: UNIFxxxx/my_uar.uar ; if the UAR is in the IFS: IFS:/home/username/uars/my_uar.uar Copy You should now be able to create and test the websrv.svc service, as described in Create and Run a Test Service on iSeries and Run the Service as a Web Service . Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}